{"word":"G2435 - ἱλαστήριον - hilastḗrion - hil-as-tay'-ree-on - Mercyseat","slug":"G2435","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">ἱλαστήριον</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>hilastḗrion"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>hil-as-tay'-ree-on"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Mercyseat"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x03B9;&#x0314;&#x03BB;&#x03B1;&#x03C3;&#x03C4;&#x03B7;&#x0301;&#x03C1;&#x03B9;&#x03BF;&#x03BD; - hilaste&#x0304;rion</b> - <i>hil-as-tay'-ree-on</i><p/>Neuter of a derivative of <a href=\"#/G2433\">G2433</a>; an <i>expiatory</i> (place or thing), that is, (concretely) an atoning <i>victim</i>, or (specifically) the <i>lid</i> of the Ark (in the Temple): - mercyseat, propitiation."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/G2433\">G2433</a>, <a href=\"#/G2434\">G2434</a>, <a href=\"#/G2436\">G2436</a>"}]}